│ THOUGHT: The crash shows a shuffle is created after its use, leading to a dominance violation. The SLP vectorizer currently sets the insertion point after the last instruction in the   │
│ bundle, which can cause newly created defs (like shuffles) to appear after uses emitted earlier in the transformation. To fix this, I will adjust BoUpSLP::setInsertPointAfterBundle to  │
│ insert before the last instruction in the bundle (or after PHIs when the last is a PHI), ensuring new instructions dominate subsequent uses.                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -n '13690,13740p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && sed -n '13714,13734p' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp | sed -n '1,200p' && sed -i               │
│ '13726,13731s/Builder.SetInsertPoint(.*/Builder.SetInsertPoint(LastInst->getParent(), LastInstIt);/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && nl -ba                           │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp | sed -n '13714,13734p' && submit-patch                                                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
